==English==
===Pronunciation===
*skĭp, /skɪp/, /<tt>skIp</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪp|Rhymes: -ɪp]]

===Verb===
[[Category:English intransitive verbs]]
[[Category:English transitive verbs]]
{{en-verb|skip|skips|skipped|skipping}}
#To [[move]] by [[hopping]] on [[alternate]] [[feet]].
#To [[leap]] [[about]] [[lightly]].
#To [[skim]], [[ricochet]] or [[bounce]] over a [[surface]].
#To [[omit]] or [[disregard]] [[intermediate]] [[item]]s or [[stage]]s.

===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
{{en-noun|skip|skips}}
#A [[leaping]], [[jumping]] or [[skipping]] movement.
#(''British'') A open-topped [[dumpster]].
#(''Australian'') (''slang, mildly derogatory'') An Australian of Anglo-Celtic descent (also [[Skippy]], see [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skippy_Australian Skippy Australian]).

